narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Fantastic explanations of leadership styles in the Full Range Leadership Model, something I have now used in regular conversation. Learned how to understand my own strengths as a leader.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Clear format, intriguing concepts led to good discussions, fun Kahoots occasionally, good slides but sometimes they were not posted on Canvas (specifically the followership one), Form 6/9 also does not appear on canvas unless you download the file and open in Adobe Acrobat.
The curriculum does not cover a lot, but it is well-organized with the modules building on each other.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! ROTC on the whole is an exceptional program which I would recommend to anyone hoping to be a leader in their future career, and this course is required for the completion of ROTC.
The only reason you would take this class is if you were AFROTC.
